; form-asm-fam-tanh-band — tanh(x) = (e^{2x} - 1)/(e^{2x} + 1) as Form->asm BYTES: the hyperbolic-tangent
; activation composed from the native exp lane, four-way + byte-identical to the M4 assembler oracle, no
; rustc/clang. tanh completes the sigmoid family on the native lane (relu, silu shipped; tanh is the sibling)
; and is the prerequisite for a native gelu-tanh, whisper's/GPT's activation.
;
; fam-silu (#3947) put silu(x)=x*sigmoid(x) on the lane; fam-tanh reuses fam-exp's ENTIRE body (range-reduce
; k+r, 2^k, degree-6 exp(r) Horner over its self-contained pool, the 2^k multiply) and wraps it in the rational
; tanh, using the e^{2x} form so NO negate encoder is needed (there is no fa-fneg):
;   prologue: fadd d0,d0,d0                        ; d0 = 2x — doubled in place, NO constant 2.0 (self-add)
;   exp(2x):  <fam-exp body>                       ; d0 = e^{2x}
;   epilogue: fmov d1,#1.0 ; fsub d2,d0,d1 (e^{2x}-1) ; fadd d1,d0,d1 (e^{2x}+1) ; fdiv d0,d2,d1 (tanh)
;   ret ; nop (8-align) ; then the 7-f64 pool
; tanh is the FIRST activation to exercise real subtraction (fa-fsub) end-to-end on hardware. The numerator
; e^{2x}-1 is computed into d2 BEFORE d1 is overwritten by the denominator (order matters); d2 is free scratch
; after exp's final poly load, and d1 held 1.0.
; ABI: d0 = x, returns d0 = tanh(x). Accuracy is fam-exp's on e^{2x} (|rel err| < ~2e-7) carried through the
; rational form, so tanh tracks the true tanh within ~2e-7 relative across the finite range (the hardware
; witness, scripts/form_asm_fam_tanh_witness.sh: bit-exact vs the exact-algorithm C mirror + close to libm tanh).
;
; The code layout is byte-for-byte the SAME LENGTH as fam-silu — a 1-word prologue (fadd d0,d0,d0 replaces
; silu's fmov d4,d0), the identical fam-exp body, a 4-word epilogue, ret, and one alignment nop = 37 code words
; (odd) + nop = 38 words. So EVERY PC-relative literal-load distance is IDENTICAL to silu's: for the n=7 pool,
; LEAD = 2n+6 = 20 and TAIL = 2n+7 = 21 (ldr d1 = 5c000281 imm19=20, tail ldr d2 = 5c0002a2 imm19=21). Exactly
; four instruction words differ from silu (word 0 prologue; words 33-35 epilogue) — each confirmed against the
; M4 assembler oracle: fadd d0,d0,d0 = 1e602800, fsub d2,d0,d1 = 1e613802, fadd d1,d0,d1 = 1e612801,
; fdiv d0,d2,d1 = 1e611840. The other 48 words are byte-identical to fam-silu's M4-proven image, and the 7-f64
; pool is the same fam-exp coefficients. 38 code words (incl. the nop) + a 56-byte 7-f64 pool = 208 bytes.
;
; Verdict 7 when every claim lands:
;   1   the composed tanh program is 208 bytes (38 code words + a 7-quad pool)          (len == 208)
;   2   the FULL 208-byte program byte-equals the M4 assembler oracle                   (fa-conviction == 1)
;   4   coefficients are DATA — f64-bytes fills the pool with the exp Taylor series      (fa-conviction == 1)
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/format-arith.fk form-stdlib/f64-bytes.fk form-stdlib/form-asm.fk form-stdlib/form-asm-matvec.fk
(do
    (let prog (fam-tanh))
    (let oracle (list
        0   40  96  30  200 95  144 210 104 165 172 242 232 168 194 242
        232 254 231 242 1   1   103 158 1   8   97  30  33  64  100 30
        41  0   120 158 232 61  135 210 72  223 191 242 72  200 197 242
        200 252 247 242 2   1   103 158 32  0   66  31  41  253 15  145
        41  45  76  211 35  1   103 158 129 2   0   92  162 2   0   92
        33  8   64  31  162 2   0   92  33  8   64  31  162 2   0   92
        33  8   64  31  162 2   0   92  33  8   64  31  162 2   0   92
        33  8   64  31  162 2   0   92  32  8   64  31  0   8   99  30
        1   16  110 30  2   56  97  30  1   40  97  30  64  24  97  30
        192 3   95  214 31  32  3   213 23  108 193 22  108 193 86  63
        17  17  17  17  17  17  129 63  85  85  85  85  85  85  165 63
        85  85  85  85  85  85  197 63  0   0   0   0   0   0   224 63
        0   0   0   0   0   0   240 63  0   0   0   0   0   0   240 63))
    (let pool-oracle (list
        23  108 193 22  108 193 86  63  17  17  17  17  17  17  129 63
        85  85  85  85  85  85  165 63  85  85  85  85  85  85  197 63
        0   0   0   0   0   0   224 63  0   0   0   0   0   0   240 63
        0   0   0   0   0   0   240 63))
    (let c1 (if (eq (len prog) 208)                                   1 0))
    (let c2 (if (eq (fa-conviction prog oracle)                  1)   2 0))
    (let c3 (if (eq (fa-conviction (fhl-pool (fam-exp-coeffs))
                                   pool-oracle)                  1)   4 0))
    (add c1 (add c2 c3)))
